meanings.definition: To sing better or more than someone else.
meanings.sent1: She outsung her friend at the karaoke competition.
meanings.sent2: The talented singer outsung all the other contestants.
meanings.sent3: The little bird outsung the big parrot in the singing contest.
meanings.sent4: Her voice outsung the sound of the crashing waves on the beach.
meanings.sent5: The choir member outsung everyone with her powerful voice.

meanings.sent1: Yesterday, she outsung her rival in the singing competition.
meanings.sent2: He outsung all his opponents in the talent show last week.
meanings.sent3: The cat outsung the dog in their musical meowing contest.
meanings.sent4: His voice outsung the howling wind during the storm.
meanings.sent5: The bird outsung the other birds with its beautiful melody.
